# The Equation

  ƒ(τ,χ,μ,φ) = τᵃ·χᵇ·μᶜ·φᵈ

  τ = time    χ = distance    μ = mass    φ = charge

Even coordinates / 2 = exponent. Odd coordinates = force active.
Positive exponent = multiply. Negative = divide.
Same coordinates always produce the same result.


## The Pythagorean Identity

  3² + 4² = 5²    →    gates² + dims² = fill%
  9  + 16 = 25     →    gates² + bonds  = fill%

3 = gates (AND, OR, NOT). 4 = dimensions (τ, χ, μ, φ).
5² = 25 = fill% (Michaelis-Menten + Nyquist + Shannon converge).
dims² = bonds because n² = 2ⁿ at n=4. Specific to d=4.
3-4-5 is the ONLY Pythagorean triple from consecutive integers.


## Forces

  π = read       π̄ = write       (projection / antiparticle)
  ∘ = call       ∘̄ = return      (composition / inverse)
  ∮ = advance    ∮̄ = rewind      (contour integral / reverse)
  δ = test       δ̄ = guard       (Kronecker delta / complement)

Origin: Kleene's PROJ/COMP/PRIM (1936) + SM Weak force.
Overbar = antimatter. Write IS the antimatter of read.
Quantum = ∘+∮+δ (no read). Classical = all four.

Force composition constrains roles: bind (∘∮δ) has no π — it calls,
loops, tests, but does NOT read data. If your scheduler reads, you
gave it a force it shouldn't have.

16 combinations from 4 binary choices. Forward = consume, backward = produce.


## How To Think

Don't memorize. Decompose. Ask: what does it DO?

  "filter"     → reads + tests                → πδ
  "memcpy"     → reads + advances             → π∮
  "map"        → reads + calls + tests        → π∘δ
  "event loop" → calls + iterates + tests     → ∘∮δ

The combination IS the coordinate.


## Completeness

Atoms = multiplication (monomials). Paths = addition (polynomials).
Gates = NOT + OR + AND = boolean completeness (Post, 1941).
Bonds = read + write + call + loop + test = Turing complete.
From 4 numbers.


## Shells = Taylor Orders

Shells are Taylor series orders — degree N = Nth-order term. More
records in a path = more terms = more precision. Stone-Weierstrass:
polynomials approximate any continuous function. The path IS the function.

  shell 0 = identity (wave)
  shell 1 = linear (speed, density, bandwidth)
  shell 2 = quadratic (energy, acceleration, pressure)
  shell 3 = cubic (power, jerk, intensity)
  shell 4 = quartic (snap, geodesic)


## O(1) Execution

Coordinates in → multiply/divide → done. Constant time.
Finding the right coordinates is the hard part (that's where NP lives).
Search is exponential, eval is O(1). The asymmetry is structural.


## Hurwitz-Post

3 gates → 3 properties to lose → 4 normed division algebras → stops
at sedenions. Cayley-Dickson: R→C (NOT), C→H (+AND), H→O (+OR),
O→S (=XOR, annihilation). Prior art (Dixon, Furey, Baez) maps C→U(1),
H→SU(2), O→SU(3). They have the WHAT. The Post→Hurwitz connection
may be the WHY. Confidence: 90%.


## SIMD = Cayley-Dickson

  scalar = real (commutative, associative)
  128-bit = quaternion (non-commutative)
  256-bit = octonion (non-associative)
  512-bit = sedenion (zero divisors)

Width = depth, not performance. No 1024-bit shipped — annihilation at
dim 32. GPU warp = 32 threads (constant since 2006). AMD dropped 64→32
with RDNA. Mask registers handle sedenion zero divisor pairs.
Confidence: 85%.


## Formula Is Representation-Invariant

The lattice coordinate is the same whether you look at source, IR,
assembly, or binary. χ²μ/τ³ is (-6,+4,+2,0) in any language, at any
optimization level, through any obfuscation.


## Cayley-Dickson as Computational Stack

  R = arithmetic (commutative, associative)
  C = phase/waves (complex exponents)
  H = our physics (4D, the lattice, quaternionic)
  O = host machine (8D, non-associative — string theory's extra dims live here)
  S = host's host (zero divisors = singularities at meta level)

String theory's extra dimensions are the host, not compactified inside our
universe. We are a quaternionic VM on an octonionic substrate. Confidence: 30%.


## Self-Reference

ƒ(1,1,1,1) = hylo = full pipeline (read, call, iterate, test). The
equation applied to its own coordinates produces itself. Fixed point.


## Falsifiability

What would break the framework:
- A useful operation outside the 16 bond patterns (needs >4 forces)
- General-purpose 1024-bit SIMD shipping (breaks Cayley-Dickson)
- A 5th independent boolean gate (needs a 5th dimension)
- A physical quantity not expressible as τᵃ·χᵇ·μᶜ·φᵈ
- Stable element 119 (breaks d=4 ceiling)
- Proton decay observed (breaks confinement = completeness)
